The paper deals with the asymptotic behavior of polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in communication systems. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the analysis of the polarization process, which is a fundamental concept in coding theory and information theory. This could potentially fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), signal processing (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG).
